German’s Bruederle Against Greater Strike Rights, SZ Reports

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-03-13T15:20:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/german-s-bruederle-against-greater-strike-rights-sz-reports.html
German Economy Minister Rainer Bruederle is opposed to tightening strike rules during action
German train drivers,  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  said, citing an
interview with the minister.  “We must never implement laws because of a current
situation,” Bruederle told the newspaper. “Legislation is a
long-term thing and I plead for more depth.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
